On Saturday 19 March 2005 13:10, Bala Krishna Kunam wrote:
> Hi,
>
> Whenever assert* or and JUnit test call fails or
> behaves unexpectedly, We need to dump the
> input/output, so that user can see why it failed or
> What happened? In case of complex data types like
> Vector or Hash Table, we need to device a way to dump
> it as well.

Well, I'm probably missing a point, but Vector and HashMap
print themselves out quite nicely already.

If they're your datatypes, define a suitable toString().

Or write your own specialised assert methods and put them in
s superclass which subclasses TestCase.
